Package: tidycps
Title: Get Basic Monthly CPS Microdata from API and Load as 'tidyverse' Ready Data Frames
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Glen", "Martin", , "glenem3@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: An integrated R interface to the United States Census Bureau's 
    Current Population Survey (CPS) API, primarily for the basic monthly CPS. Allow R users to return the 
    basic monthly CPS microdata as tidyverse-ready data frames. Includes additional functions to transform various 
    CPS variables into indicators for ease in generating nationally representative weighted estimates.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Imports: 
    dplyr,
    glue,
    httr2,
    jsonlite,
    lubridate,
    stringr,
    utils
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5)
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/glenem/tidycps
BugReports: https://github.com/glenem/tidycps/issues
